%description:
TCP Fast Open (RFC 7413) F3.2: an app calls connect(fastOpen=true) with a
cookie already cached (connection 1 primes the cache, as in
tcp_fastopen_1.test) but never SENDs on connection 2 -- the deferred SYN
must not hang forever. The connEstabTimer's safety net fires at the normal
TCP_TIMEOUT_CONN_ESTAB (75s) and sends the fallback bare SYN, still
carrying the cached cookie (RFC 7413 explicitly allows a data-less SYN
with a valid cookie), instead of aborting the connection as a genuine
establishment timeout would.

Falsification: without this commit's fix, no SYN goes out at all past
75s -- the connEstabTimer fires straight into process_TIMEOUT_CONN_ESTAB(),
which treats it as a real timeout and refuses the connection (verified on
the pre-fix tree: cli_tcp transitions SYN_SENT --> CLOSED instead of
sending a second SYN).

%inifile: omnetpp.ini
[General]
record-vector-results = false
ned-path = .;../../../../src;../../lib
sim-time-limit = 76s

network = inet.test.moduletest.lib.TcpTestNet1

cmdenv-event-banners=false
cmdenv-express-mode=false
cmdenv-log-prefix="[%c]: "

*.testing=false
*.tcptester.script=""

*.cli_app.localAddress="10.0.0.1"
*.cli_app.localPort=1000
*.cli_app.connectAddress="10.0.0.2"
*.cli_app.connectPort=2000
*.cli_app.active=true
*.cli_app.tOpen=0s
*.cli_app.tSend=-1s
*.cli_app.sendBytes=0B
*.cli_app.tClose=-1s
*.cli_app.sendScript=""
*.cli_app.fastOpen=true
*.cli_app.active2=true
*.cli_app.tOpen2=0.5s
*.cli_app.localPort2=1001
*.cli_app.tSend2=-1s
*.cli_app.sendBytes2=0B
*.cli_app.fastOpen2=true

*.srv_app.localAddress="10.0.0.2"
*.srv_app.localPort=2000
*.srv_app.connectAddress="10.0.0.1"
*.srv_app.connectPort=1000
*.srv_app.active=false
*.srv_app.tOpen=0s
*.srv_app.tSend=-1s
*.srv_app.sendBytes=0B
*.srv_app.tClose=-1s
*.srv_app.sendScript=""
*.srv_app.active2=false
*.srv_app.tOpen2=0.5s
*.srv_app.localPort2=2000

*.*_tcp.sackSupport = false
*.*_tcp.windowScalingSupport = false
*.*_tcp.timestampSupport = false
*.*_tcp.mss = 1000
*.*_tcp.tcpAlgorithmClass = "TcpReno"

*.cli_tcp.fastopenClientEnabled = true
*.srv_tcp.fastopenServerEnabled = true
*.srv_tcp.fastopenLenientCookieValidation = false

include ../../lib/tcp-legacy.ini

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%file: postrun.pl
open FILE, '<test.out';
while($sor = <FILE>)
{
    if ($sor =~ /^\[testing\]: (.*)$/)
    {
        print "$1\n";
    }
}
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%postrun-command:  perl ./postrun.pl
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# Connection 1: bare cookie-request SYN, learned by the client (same as tcp_fastopen_1.test).
%contains: postrun-command(1).out
[0.001 A001] A.1000 > B.2000: S 0:0(0) win 7504   Option(s): MaxSegSize NOP NOP FastOpen(cookieLen=0)
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%contains: postrun-command(1).out
[0.003 B001] A.1000 < B.2000: A S 500:500(0) ack 1 win 7504   Option(s): MaxSegSize NOP NOP FastOpen(cookieLen=8)
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# Connection 2: the deferred SYN's ISS is picked at connect() time (t=0.5s, when
%# selectInitialSeqNum() runs), so this exact "[75.501 A003] ... S 125000:..." line can
%# only appear if the SYN was actually held back until the connEstabTimer safety net
%# fired at t=0.5+75=75.5s -- an earlier (regressed) transmission would show a
%# different ISS (selectInitialSeqNum() is simTime()-derived) at a different timestamp.
%contains: postrun-command(1).out
[75.501 A003] A.1001 > B.2000: S 125000:125000(0) win 7504   Option(s): MaxSegSize NOP NOP FastOpen(cookieLen=8)
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%postrun-command: grep "undisposed object:" test.out > test_undisposed.out || true
%not-contains: test_undisposed.out
undisposed object: (
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
